# The Internet - Web Development: Lesson 7 - Introduction to Styling with CSS

## Background

This lesson introduces CSS as a way to style elements on the page. Students learn the basic syntax for CSS rules and then explore color properties, text properties, image properties and border properties. They work on a HTML page about Guinness World Record holders, adding additional style properties in each level. In the last level, students are given a checklist to use as they apply what theyâ€™ve learned to their About Me page.
# Vocabulary

* **CSS** - CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. CSS allows each HTML element to be styled according to certain set of rules.
* **CSS Selector** - Specifies the part of the code which the style should be applied to.
* **Documentation** - a description of the behavior of a command, function, library, API, etc.


# New Blocks

## HTML

* **Head** - `<head></head>`
* **Body** - `<body></body>`
* **Style** - `<style></style>`
* **Title** - `<title></title>`

## CSS
* **Color** - `color: value;`
* **Background Color** - `background-color: value;`
* **Text Align** - `text-align: value;`
* **Text Decoration** - `text-decoration: value;`
* **Width** - `width: value;`
* **Height** - `height: value;`
* **Border Color** - `border-color: value;`
* **Border Style** - `border-style: value;`
* **Border Width** - `border-width: value;`

